Step 1: Create Input Files

Compression Input File (input.txt): Create a file named input.txt with the following content:

AAAABBBCCDAA

Decompression Input File (compressed.txt): Create a file named compressed.txt with the following content (this is what you would get after compressing input.txt):

4A3B2C1D2A

Step 2: Run the Program

Compile the Program: Save the provided C code in a file named rle_compression.c and compile it using a C compiler:

gcc rle_compression.c -o rle_compression

Run the Program: Execute the program:

./rle_compression

Step 3: Compression Example

User Input:


Run-Length Encoding (RLE) Compression Tool

1. Compress a file

2. Decompress a file

Enter your choice: 1

Enter the input file name: input.txt

Enter the output file name: compressed.txt

Expected Output:


File compressed successfully.
Content of compressed.txt after compression:


4A3B2C1D2A

Step 4: Decompression Example

Run the Program Again: Execute the program again:


./rle_compression

User Input:

Run-Length Encoding (RLE) Compression Tool

1. Compress a file

2. Decompress a file

Enter your choice: 2

Enter the input file name: compressed.txt

Enter the output file name: decompressed.txt

Expected Output:

File decompressed successfully.
